text: Adán Gordón (21 January 1906 - 8 March 1966) was a Panamanian swimmer. He competed in two events at the 1928 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1906 births Category:1966 deaths Category:People from Taboga District Category:Panamanian male swimmers Category:Olympic swimmers of Panama Category:Swimmers at the 1928 Summer Olympics Category:Place of death missing
